sf_description: Non-heap memory used by masters
Comparison of busy executors to pending jobs
The charts on the right indicate status of resources related to jobs

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
The charts on the right

* `Slave Status`: shows the online status of all configured slaves
* `Busy Executors vs Pending Jobs`: as the name suggests, its a comparison of current queue size vs executors in-use. This will help decide if the available slots are enough for the number of jobs Jenkins is handling
* `Average Duration - Past Day`: shows the top 5 builds that have a high average build duration
* `Top 5 Failed Jobs`: shows the top 5 failed jobs in the past day. In use with `Job Failure Rate` will provide great insights into the reasons and help narrow down problems quickly

sf_description: These charts on the right show Jenkins masters' stats

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
The charts on the right  

* `Alive Status`: shows whether a master is online or not
* `Health Score`: shows the mean health score for a master. Any number below 1 means a health-check has failed and specific health-check can be verified in the `Jenkins Master` dashboard
* `Job Failure Rate`: shows ratio of failed to completed jobs. Completed jobs are categorized as `SUCCESS`, `NOT_BUILT`, `UNSTABLE`
* `Executor Usage`: shows the usage % of all executors available
